  "market_context": "NQ daily chart shows price approaching equal highs that have not yet been swept, setting up buy-side liquidity as a target for the upcoming week. A protected swing low formed after price reached into a fair value gap and closed through it.",
  "key_observation": "Monday opposes the bullish weekly bias, then Tuesday forms a candle two closure inside a fair value gap with an opposing candle, confirmed by hourly change in state of delivery — enabling anticipation of Wednesday and Thursday as expansion days.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify equal highs above current price on the daily NQ chart, establishing buy-side liquidity as the weekly draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 2: Note the protected swing low formed when price reached into a fair value gap, retested, and closed through it.",
    "Step 3: Observe Monday opening and opposing the anticipated bullish weekly bias — desirable behavior for a low-of-week to form.",
    "Step 4: Recognize Monday alone is not yet a candle two closure since the weekly low cannot be confirmed yet.",
    "Step 5: Tuesday delivers a candle two closure inside the fair value gap with an opposing candle, marking the low of week.",
    "Step 6: Drop to the hourly timeframe and confirm a change in state of delivery by price closing through the series of down-close candles at the low.",
    "Step 7: Anticipate Wednesday (candle three) expansion higher — price consolidates, sweeps, and expands up.",
    "Step 8: With Wednesday's strong close, anticipate Thursday (candle four) as a continuation expansion higher.",
    "Step 9: After two large expansion days and a weaker Thursday close, avoid anticipating a third expansion day on Friday."
  ],
  "outcome": "Both Wednesday and Thursday expanded higher as anticipated, delivering the classic expansion weekly profile toward the equal highs target.",
  "lessons": "Pairing a weekly candle two closure (Tuesday low) inside a daily fair value gap with hourly change in state of delivery allows high-probability anticipation of Wednesday and Thursday expansion. Avoid chasing a third expansion day after weekly range is largely complete.",
